Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_pll_cl...e_driving_cell(25.10)    timing_pll_cl...e_driving_cell(25.10)

Name
       timing_pll_clock_use_driving_cell

Syntax
       timing_pll_clock_use_driving_cell

       {true | false}

       Default : false

       Uses  delay calculation of all the enabled arcs to the PLL clock output
       to compute the transition.

       When set to true, the delay calculation of all enabled arcs to the  PLL
       clock output will be used to compute the transition. If no driving arcs
       are  available in the model or if they are disabled, the same idealized
       transition will be used.

       When set to false, the software considers the PLL clock  output  to  be
       electrically  isolated from the input-side reference clock, and creates
       the output clock with an idealized transition. You can use the  set_an-
       notated_transition command to customize the output clock transition.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

